female and 69% male, whose pay 
rates are set by the clients they work 
for. The median pay gap is 0.1% as 
there were a large number of 
temporary colleagues, both male on 
the same hourly pay rates.  
The second table shows that male 
staff are more likely to be paid a 
bonus than males, however this is 
because males make up a greater 
proportion of our temporary 
workforce who are less likely to earn 
bonus. 

