Our results for 2017

The charts below show the percentage of male and female colleagues that are contained 
within each pay quartile band.  There are two sets of charts, one for all staff (as required 
by the regulations), and the other for our salaried for our salaried colleagues only.
Almost all salaried staff sit within the upper two pay quartiles, with females representing 
54% of the salaried staff population and therefore showing females as having a greater 
representation within these quartiles, albeit overall salaried male staff achieve a higher 
average rate of pay and bonus pay as more are employed in middle and senior 
management roles.
